A [[Subnet|Subnetwork]] is a [[Layer 3|Network Layer]] concept, while [[VLANs|VLAN]] are [[Layer 2|Datalink Layer]] - so they are handled separately.

It is standard good practice to not try to put devices from different [[Subnets|Subnetwork]] into the same [[VLAN]] - although technically it is possible